-- EU Says Greece on Track With Cuts, Repayment Extension Not Being Discussed
-- B y   J a m e s   G .   N e u g e r
-- 2010-10-12T10:30:26Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/eu-says-greece-on-track-on-deficit-cuts-sees-no-talk-of-repayment-delay.html
Greece is living up to its deficit-
cut pledges and there is no discussion of giving it extra time
to repay European Union and International Monetary Fund loans,
the European Commission said.  “Greece is on track,” commission spokesman Amadeu Altafaj
told reporters in Brussels today. “The market is reacting
positively. There is no case to envisage such an extension.”  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James Neuger at 
 jneuger@bloomberg.net  